name: integer_u32_binary32_max_safe_integer
description: |
  This is 2^24 - 1, the largest integer for which every integer through that
  magnitude is distinct in IEEE 754 binary32. The next integer is exactly
  representable but no longer safe because binary32 has 24 bits of significand
  precision.
format: hex
decode-as: u32
pair:
  - with: binary32-exact-boundary.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "binary32"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "safe-integer"
  - "precision"
  - "boundary"
  - "off-by-one"
---
ff ff ff 00 # 16777215 (2^24 - 1)
